{"id":38547,"title":"Management of maple syrup urine disease in the peri-operative period.","abstract":"Maple syrup urine disease (MSUD) has an incidence of 1:125,000 newborns in Ireland. Patients, when fasting, or in a catabolic state build up toxic metabolites leading to progressive neurological dysfunction. We describe the necessary peri-operative management of a patient with MSUD who developed symptomatic gallstones requiring a laparoscopic cholecystectomy.","date":"2014-01-14","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24416851","annotations":[{"name":"Disease","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Urine","weight":0.775297,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urine"},{"name":"Catabolism","weight":0.748891,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catabolism"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.675547,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxicity"},{"name":"Gallstone","weight":0.58336,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallstone"},{"name":"Incidence (epidemiology)","weight":0.574584,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incidence_(epidemiology)"},{"name":"Neurology","weight":0.551844,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurology"},{"name":"Fasting","weight":0.502939,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fasting"},{"name":"Maple syrup urine disease","weight":0.469348,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maple_syrup_urine_disease"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.418173,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Ireland","weight":0.294258,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ireland"},{"name":"Metabolite","weight":0.289179,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolite"},{"name":"Laparoscopic surgery","weight":0.200993,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laparoscopic_su